<hl>
<seg id=1> An American multinational corporation is going to open a chain of three hundred super market stores in Fujian </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Xiamen, January 16th, by Yinrui Yu- Two convenient stores, named "Beishun", are opening for business here today. </seg>
<seg id=3> This represents the official beginning of Xianmen Funanpuli Super Stores Ltd., in which a large American multinational corporation, Bitoz?? , holds 60% of the company shares. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Xianmen Funanpuli Super Stores Ltd., co-operated by American Bitoz?? International group, Xiamen(Chian) Foreign Trade & Supply Corporation and Feili Global International Company, is the first sino-foreign joint venture retail store in Fujian province. </seg>
<seg id=5> According to the agreement, the total amount of investment in this project is 26,000,000 US dollars; the amount of the first stage investment is 10,000,000 US dollar. Twenty demonstration convenient stores and a modern supply center will be opened in Xiamen followed by three hundred convenient stores in succession in nine cities of Fujian province along with the local market development. </seg>
<seg id=6> These stores usually locate in crowed residential areas, the size of each large store is approximately 400 square meters, selling daily necessities, groceries and accessories that residents need the most in household. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> American Bitoz International Industry Ltd. is a large food multinational company with an annual sales volume of over 2.1 billion US dollars. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The Chinese opening up policies toward retail industries are relatively cautious. Currently, they only have demonstration stores operating in Beijing, Qindao, Daliang, GuangZhou, Shezhen, Wuhan, Shanghai, etc., etc.  American Bitoz International Industries Limited's opening of these stores in China is one of the most major foreign investments in the Chinese retail industry. </seg>
</p>
